  "description": "The Wild Mediterranean Garden at 1 Flinders Avenue is a purpose-driven, biophilic and naturalistic garden adapted to the filtered light and microclimate of this site — particularly the shifting dappled shade beneath a mature deciduous Chinese Elm. A layered palette combining Mediterranean structure with dryland meadow softness and local ecological function. Plants selected for resilience, visual rhythm, seasonal interest, and support for pollinators and beneficial insects. New soil, mulch and shaped topography build ecological function from the ground up.",
